African National Congress (ANC) national executive committee member Tony Yengeni’s house in Cape Town burned down on Monday morning. City of Cape Town Fire and Rescue spokesperson Theo Layne confirmed they responded to the emergency call at 04h30 on Monday morning. He said the cause of the fire at the house in the Tygerhof Estate had not yet been determined, and the case had been handed over to the South African Police Services for further investigation. Layne said Yengeni’s mother, who had been the only person home when the fire started, sustained no injuries, as she managed to get out of the house in time. – Caxton News Service Read original story on citizen.co.za